# ========================================
# Repository Size Policy
# ========================================
# This repository enforces a 1MB file size limit to prevent bloat.
#
# History: In Nov 2024, we cleaned the repo from 240MB to 26MB by removing
# accidentally committed node_modules (docs/site/node_modules/).
#
# Enforcement:
# - Pre-commit hook blocks files >1MB locally (.git/hooks/pre-commit)
# - GitHub Actions check blocks large files in PRs
#
# If you need to commit large files:
# - Use .gitignore for build artifacts (node_modules, binaries, etc.)
# - Use Git LFS for binary assets (images, videos, datasets)
# - Host externally for very large files (S3, CDN, package registries)
#
# To bypass the pre-commit hook (NOT recommended):
# git commit --no-verify
# ========================================

